message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper deals with image segmentation using deep neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also introduces a novel few-shot learning framework, which involves training a model with only a few annotated examples, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The application of the proposed framework is in the medical domain, specifically in volumetric medical image segmentation, which makes it relevant to the medical imaging (cs.MED) category. Finally, the paper proposes a new architecture that incorporates 'squeeze & excite' blocks, which are inspired by neuroscience, making it relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NEURON) category.
